Variability.
The preoccipital furrow is usually absent, but it can appear as a faint impression (USN- MENT 
01212999
, PSUC_ 
FEM 34079
). There is also color variation, especially with the age of the specimens. Fresher specimens tend to have a dark brown head, darker than the mesosoma (UCRC_ENT 00103618, UCRC_ ENT 00103621), whereas in older specimens, the head tends to be light brown and can even appear of similar color to the mesosoma (MCZ-ENT711742, USNMENT 
01212999
). This is likely a result of the specimen coloration fading over time (see 
Fig. 25
).
